Position overview

Permanent, Full-time opportunity

About us
We're on a mission to create a brighter future, where you can be a change maker at the actual source. We're one of Australia's largest water utilities with over 30% of Victoria's population relying on us for their essential water and sanitation services.

Our award-winning culture fosters an inclusive, collaborative, and flexible environment that enables our people to thrive. Here, you'll be inspired and challenged to grow alongside us.

We're committed to reconciliation and supporting the self-determined role for Traditional Owners/Custodians in water and land management.

The Role
The AI Lead Engineer plays a strategic and influential role in advancing the organisation's data and AI capability within the Enterprise Data & Analytics function. The role drives business value and enterprise performance by designing, developing, and operationalising AI and machine learning solutions that inform decision-making, optimise operations, and enable predictive and prescriptive insights across Asset Services, Asset Transformation & Technology, and other critical enterprise domains.

Working closely with Architects, Enterprise Data and Analytics leads, and business stakeholders, the AI Lead Engineer ensures AI initiatives are strategically aligned to organisational objectives, technically robust, and deliver measurable outcomes, including efficiency gains, risk mitigation, and enhanced service delivery. The role champions the adoption of Databricks, Azure, and modern AI frameworks to accelerate intelligent automation, enable actionable insights, and embed innovation across the organisation, positioning AI as a driver of enterprise strategy and long-term value creation.

Your key responsibilities

AI Model Development and Innovation - Drive the development and deployment of advanced AI/ML solutions using NLP, transformers, LLMs, and generative AI to deliver business value, improve decision-making, and enable intelligent automation. Leverage cloud platforms and enterprise data tools for scalable, reusable, and rapid AI innovation while fostering continuous improvement and adoption across the organisation.
AI Engineering and Operationalisation - Design, deploy and operate scalable, secure MLOps pipelines that support the full AI lifecycle from experimentation to production, ensuring high-quality, auditable and cost-effective models. Establish AI engineering standards and best practices, automate deployment using DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code, and collaborate with data and software engineering teams to seamlessly integrate AI solutions into enterprise systems and workflows.
Governance, Risk and Responsible AI - Establish and enforce responsible AI governance, standards and validation processes to ensure AI solutions are ethical, explainable, auditable and compliant, working closely with risk, data governance and security teams to enable safe and trusted AI adoption.
Strategy Alignment and Influence - Align AI initiatives with organisational strategy and architecture, influence enterprise AI direction and standards, and translate complex AI concepts into clear, actionable insights for stakeholders.
Leadership, Culture and Capability Uplift - Provide technical leadership and mentorship to uplift AI capability, lead cross-functional teams to deliver AI outcomes, and promote a collaborative, learning-focused culture of responsible AI adoption.

What we're looking for

Strong background in software or data engineering using Python and/or TypeScript
Hands-on experience with Databricks Machine Learning, including MLflow, AutoML, Delta Lake and Spark
Proven experience building machine learning and deep learning models using TensorFlow, PyTorch and Scikit-learn
Solid understanding of MLOps practices, including model tracking, deployment, monitoring and CI/CD
Experience working with cloud platforms, preferably Azure, including Databricks Lakehouse and Unity Catalog
Practical experience with transformer-based and generative AI technologies (LLMs, LangChain, LlamaIndex, Semantic Kernel)
Strong data engineering skills, including Spark/PySpark, Delta Lake and production-grade data pipelines
Experience applying DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code practices using Docker, Kubernetes/AKS, Terraform and CI/CD pipelines
Demonstrated ability to design and deliver AI/ML solutions such as chatbots, summarisation and intelligent automation
Tertiary qualifications in a relevant discipline or equivalent Technical Qualification in Engineering or IT
